{{Quote|You may hate the dictator, but [[Council of Kangs|something]]... far worse is gonna fill that void if you depose of him. I've lived a million lifetimes. I've gone through every, every scenario. [[Time Variance Authority|This]] is the only way.|He Who Remains to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and [[Sylvie Laufeydottir]]|For All Time. Always.}}
'''{{ConjecNameAU|Victor Timely}}''' was a scientist from the 31st Century who came into contact with alternate universes and other versions of himself. When some of these Variants attempted to conquer other realities, a [[Multiversal War]] ensued, which he ended by weaponizing [[Alioth]]. Under the moniker of '''He Who Remains''', he founded and ruled the [[Time Variance Authority]] to preserve the [[Sacred Timeline]] and prevent the return of his [[Council of Kangs|counterparts]]. Residing at the [[Citadel at the End of Time]] for eons, He Who Remains planned for [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and [[Sylvie Laufeydottir]] to succeed him as the TVA leaders, but the latter killed him, which resulted in the fracturing of the [[Multiverse]] and the return of his Variants.

However, he had a contingency plan to have himself resurrected. The plan went into effect following his "death." The chain of events afterwards eventually led to Loki [[Time Slipping]] to just before he was killed, as he intended. He Who Remains then explains this was all part of his plan and tells him to work with him to preserve the timeline. Unfortunately, his plan failed when Loki instead went back to his time, destroyed the [[Temporal Loom]] and became the one to hold the branches together, ultimatley resulting in He Who Remains' permamnent death and failed plan.

==Biography==
===[[Multiversal War]]===
{{MD|He Who Remains (Earth-TRN870)}}
====Defeating His Variants====
{{Quote|I harnessed the beast's power and began experimenting on it. I weaponized [[Alioth]] and I ended... I ended the [[Multiversal War]].|He Who Remains|For All Time. Always.}}
[[File:HWR Presentation.png|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains weaponizes [[Alioth]]]]
While living on [[Earth]] in the 31st century, Victor Timely, who was a scientist, discovered the existence of the [[Multiverse]], which consisted of alternate universes and alternate versions of himself. He caused them to meet each other leading to them sharing their knowledge and technology with one another, creating a temporary peace. During this time, he also created an AI he named [[Miss Minutes]] to serve as his assistant{{Ref|LK106}} and chess partner. Knowing that Miss Minutes was capable of more, he allowed her to write her own code, though consistently denied her a body.{{Ref|LK203}} Some of his Variants, such as [[Kang the Conqueror]], saw the alternate universes as places to rule over, thus starting the [[Multiversal War]].{{Ref|LK106}} During the war, Timely had a Variant of [[Rebecca Tourminet]], who he named [[Ravonna Renslayer]], leading his army.{{Ref|LK204}} He discovered a monster created from the rifts of space-time, whom he dubbed [[Alioth]], and harnessed its power to defeat his Variants, ending the war.{{Ref|LK106}}

====Preserving Peace====
[[File:Sacred Timeline.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains oversees the [[Sacred Timeline]]]]
{{Quote|You are quite a marvel. I will be proud to lead with you. You made a difference in this war. Thank you for being on my team.|He Who Remains to [[Ravonna Renslayer]]|Ouroboros (episode)}}
Isolating a collection of timelines that followed the same baseline, which he titled the [[Sacred Timeline]],<ref name="SacredTimeline">[https://screencrush.com/michael-waldron-interview-loki-heels/ ''Creator Michael Waldron Answers All Our Questions About ‘Loki’ And ‘Heels’'']</ref> he wrote a strict script to be followed, eliminating branches that did not follow his script for the Sacred Timeline.{{Ref|LK106}} He Who Remains also created the [[Temporal Loom]], a device created to manage and eventually delete branched timelines if they had not been pruned in time as a failsafe to ensure the Sacred Timeline's existence.{{Ref|LK206}} Now operating under the moniker He Who Remains, he created the [[Time Variance Authority]] to govern and protect it from being overrun by his surviving Variants. He captured Variants from branched timelines and erased their memories of their lives, brainwashing them to serve as employees of the TVA, including positions such as field agents and analysts, and instilling in them the desire to prune rogue timelines and preserve multiversal peace.{{Ref|LK106}}
[[File:Kang Statue.png|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains' statue at the [[Time Variance Authority Office|TVA Office]]]]
Under his new rule, he worked alongside [[Ravonna Renslayer]] to help run the TVA,{{Ref|LK204}} with its employees aware that they were working for him.{{Ref|LK201}} He Who Remains located an asteroid at the end of time and established a castle there, called the [[Citadel at the End of Time]], from which he watched over the Sacred Timeline.{{Ref|LK106}} As the Citadel neared completion, Renslayer and He Who Remains admired it and their mission. He Who Remains complimented Renslayer's efforts in the war and declared his pride to lead alongside her.
[[File:He Who Remains and A-23 Partnership.png|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains and [[Ravonna Renslayer]] work together]]
Renslayer opened a [[Timedoor]] to the [[Time Variance Authority Office]] and noted that the organization was awaiting commands. He Who Remains said that he would catch up and let her go through the Timedoor alone. He Who Remains then summoned [[Miss Minutes]] and ordered her to initiate one of his protocols, which would erase all memories and traces of him from the TVA and its employees. Miss Minutes hesitantly agreed and followed out the order, and He Who Remains silently apologized to Renslayer.{{Ref|LK204}} He then created the three android [[Time-Keepers]] to publicly serve as the TVA founders. He also tasked Miss Minutes to create false history of the TVA as propaganda.{{Ref|LK106}}

===[[Attack on the Citadel at the End of Time|Attack on the Citadel]]===
[[File:He Who Remains reveals himself.png|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains reveals himself to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and [[Sylvie Laufeydottir|Sylvie]]]]
{{Quote|I'm tired. And I'm older. I'm older than I look. This game is for the young, the hungry. I've gone through a lot of scenarios... trying to find the right person to take this spot. It turns out that person came in two.|He Who Remains to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and [[Sylvie Laufeydottir]]|For All Time. Always.}}
Millennia later,<ref>[https://thedirect.com/article/loki-kang-deleted-scenes ''Loki: Deleted 'Kang' Scenes From Finale Revealed'']</ref> He Who Remains grew tired of his endless work and responsibility and wanted to find a new successor. He guided a [[Loki]] [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Variant]] that he allowed to exist as well as a female Loki Variant named [[Sylvie Laufeydottir]] through their adventures and paved their road leading to him.{{Ref|LK106}} However, knowing what Laufeydottir had planned for him, He Who Remains created a contingency plan, a portion of which included having [[Miss Minutes]] create a [[Victor Timely]] Variant in [[Before 20th Century#1868|1868]], which he informed her about.{{Ref|LK206}} When Loki and Laufeydottir approached his castle, he invited them in to speak with him. When Laufeydottir called him He Who Remains, he laughed that Miss Minutes was still referring to him as that, but said that he liked the name.
[[File:Loki106 0341.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains evades [[Sylvie Laufeydottir|Laufeydottir]]'s attacks repeatedly]]
He tried to speak with Loki and Laufeydottir in the elevator, but Laufeydottir was too intent on revenge and tried to kill him repeatedly. However, he evaded her using his [[TemPad]], and transported himself to his office. He invited Loki and Laufeydottir into his office to sit down in chairs in front of his table and offered them drinks.
[[File:He explains.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains explains the [[Multiversal War]] and the [[TVA]]]]
Eventually, the duo sat down, and he told them that he knew everything that would happen, showing them a printed transcript of the very dialogue they had just uttered. He then told them about the history about his Variants, the Multiversal War, [[Alioth]], and why he created the [[Time Variance Authority]]. He informed the pair that not all of his Variants were like him, with some being evil and bent on conquering realities.
[[File:He Who Remains new image 5.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains telling [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and [[Sylvie Laufeydottir|Laufeydottir]] about time]]
He informed Loki and Laufeydottir that their recent actions leading to him had been designed by him, including their adventures on [[Lamentis-1]] and in the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]] and that he wanted to be sure that it was them who could take his place. Claiming that he was much older than he looked and was tired, he asked them to take his place to be in charge of the TVA and to oversee the protection of the Sacred Timeline. He offered them two choices: kill him and let the Sacred Timeline expand into the [[Multiverse]], thereby letting his Variants wreak havoc before he eventually returned in some form; or become his successors and ultimately the leaders of the TVA.{{Ref|LK106}} However, not truly intending to die at Laufeydottir's hand, He Who Remains enacted his secret contingency plan.{{Ref|LK206}}
[[File:He doesnt lie.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains learns they crossed the threshold]]
As thunder crackled above, he told Loki and Laufeydottir that they had just crossed the threshold,{{Ref|LK106}} and lied to the pair{{Ref|LK206}} by telling them that he was no longer able to determine the future. He Who Remains then witnessed Laufeydottir and Loki duel each other, as Loki was trying to stop her from immediately killing He Who Remains. He witnessed as the two Loki Variants kissed before Laufeydottir used He Who Remains' [[TemPad]] to throw Loki out of the Citadel through a [[Timedoor]].{{Ref|LK106}}
[[File:Sylive realizes.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Timely is stabbed and killed by [[Sylvie Laufeydottir|Laufeydottir]]]] 
Unbeknownst to Laufeydottir, He Who Remains had arranged for her to commit this very action, as it granted Loki the ability to [[Time Slipping|time slip]], with in conjunction with his order to have Miss Minutes create a [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely Variant]] served as his contingency plan to be resurrected.{{Ref|LK206}} He Who Remains then told Laufeydottir that he was impressed, before she threw his table aside and stabbed him in the chest. He winked at her, however, and cryptically told her that he would see her soon, before laughing and dying.{{Ref|LK106}}

===Legacy===
====The Return of the Kang Dynasty====
{{Quote|Someone is coming. Countless different versions of a [[Hub:Victor Timely|very dangerous person]]. And they're all set on [[Multiversal War|war]]. [[Time Variance Authority|We]] need to prepare.|[[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]|For All Time. Always.}}
With He Who Remains' death, the [[Sacred Timeline]] was reconnected to the greater [[Multiverse]] and numerous branching realities were rapidly created, which allowed the [[Council of Kangs]] to gain access to the Sacred Timeline. When [[Kang the Conqueror]] was killed during a [[Uprising in Axia|fight]] with [[Ant-Man]], the Council concluded that the heroes of Earth were getting too close to destroying the Multiversal dynasty they had built and summoned every Variant of theirs in existence to assemble in order to stop them.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

[[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] found himself in the past of the [[Time Variance Authority]], which only sped up the creation of branching timelines.{{Ref|LK106}}<ref name="Herron">[https://www.btlnews.com/crafts/direction/loki-director-kate-herron/ Director Kate Herron Reveals Secrets of the Loki Universe (Spoilers Ahead!!)]</ref> Loki's experience with He Who Remains left a big impact on him, as he went on to describe He Who Remains as a dangerous and terrifying figure. As he and [[Mobius M. Mobius]] traveled to the branched timeline where the [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely Variant]] resided, Loki became fearful at the prospect of Timely being as dangerous as He Who Remains was.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====Posthumous Plans====
=====Victor Timely's Role=====
[[File:Skeleton He Who Remains.png|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains' corpse]]
{{Quote|Tell me, how is [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor T-T-Timely]]?"<br>"Of course you know about your..."<br>"Wait. Don't tell me. You're, you're having some, some, some problems with the [[Temporal Loom]].|He Who Remains and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]|Glorious Purpose (Loki Season Two)}}
As He Who Remains' body began to decompose in his chair,{{Ref|LK203}} the [[Time Variance Authority]] stopped pruning branched timelines, causing the [[Temporal Loom]] to overload. At the same time, [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] began [[Time Slipping|time slipping]], an affliction granted to him by He Who Remains that had the trickster god uncontrollably transported across various points in time,{{Ref|LK201}} while [[Miss Minutes]] set out to enact her role in He Who Remains' contingency plan. Amassing a file on [[Victor Timely]]'s whereabouts, she arranged for [[Ravonna Renslayer]] to meet with her in [[Before 20th Century#1868|1868]] in [[Chicago]], where Timely, who was He Who Remains' [[Sacred Timeline]] counterpart, resided. He Who Remains' orders consisted of the pair giving the ''[[Time Variance Authority Official Handbook]]'' to Timely as a child, thereby creating a branched timeline and rendering the [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|version]] of Timely who received the book as a [[Glossary#Variant|Variant]] who would study the science of the TVA.

Miss Minutes and Renslayer believed that He Who Remains' intent was to have this Timely Variant become his successor; however, when Timely rejected Miss Minutes' romantic advances, she decided not to honor He Who Remains' wishes and chose to turn on Timely.{{Ref|LK203}} Additionally, Miss Minutes showed Renslayer a video of He Who Remains ordering her memories to be wiped, which resulted in Renslayer joining Miss Minutes in the belief that He Who Remains did not deserve to have his Variant succeed him. These actions caused the pair to go against the supposed contingency plan by deciding to rule over the TVA themselves.{{Ref|LK204}}

Unbeknownst to them, He Who Remains had arranged for this very scenario, as his true intent for the creation of the Timely Variant was not for Timely to work with Renslayer and Miss Minutes to become his successor; instead, the true plan was for Timely to be recruited by Loki and the TVA as a means to fix the Temporal Loom, knowing full well that Timely would not succeed and that the destruction of several realities would prompt Loki to time slip before [[Sylvie Laufeydottir]] killed He Who Remains, thereby undoing his death and essentially resurrecting him.{{Ref|LK206}}

=====Brief Resurrection=====
[[File:HWR Taunts and Laughs.png|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains is saved by [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
{{Quote|Kiddo, did you really think I was just gonna sit back and let [[Sylvie Laufeydottir|her]] kill me? And that'd be it? Zip? Nada? RIP HWR? No, I told you. Reincarnation, baby.|He Who Remains to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]|Glorious Purpose (Loki Season Two)}}
With [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]] unable to scale the [[Temporal Loom]] to handle infinite branches, despite [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] having lived through centuries and having rewound time multiple times, Loki came to the conclusion that the only way to protect reality was to prevent [[Sylvie Laufeydottir]] from [[Attack on the Citadel at the End of Time|killing]] He Who Remains. Loki then [[Time Slipping|time slipped]] back to the [[Citadel at the End of Time]] before Laufeydottir could kill him, thereby resurrecting He Who Remains in the temporal sense and fulfilling He Who Remains' true contingency plan. Loki attempted to convince Laufeydottir not to kill He Who Remains, although she refused to listen and stabbed He Who Remains. Loki then rewound time and unsuccessfully failed to convince Laufeydottir again, and continued to rewind time after each failed attempt in order to resurrect He Who Remains.
[[File:He Who Remains (Glorious Purpose).png|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains talks to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
Loki eventually asked He Who Remains why he sat by and watched Laufeydottir try to kill him without bothering to defend himself. He Who Remains then used his [[TemPad]] to freeze Laufeydottir in time and asked Loki how many times he had rewound time trying to save him. When Loki expressed shock at Laufeydottir being frozen, He Who Remains replied that he was surprised that Loki hadn't gained that ability yet. He Who Remains then divulged that he had paved the road for Loki to gain his time slipping ability for the sole purpose of resurrecting him, disclosing that he never intended for Laufeydottir to permanently kill him and adding that everything that Loki had gone through of late was part of the contingency plan that he had created to ensure his return. Noting Loki's lack of retort, He Who Remains told Loki that since this was too much for the trickster god to process, he would restore Laufeydottir's agency and that perhaps after a couple thousand more loops, Loki would be ready to have a conversation.
[[File:He Who Remains Smile.png|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains smiles at [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
However, Loki then paused Laufeydottir in time, not only revealing that he indeed had that ability, but that they had already had this conversation. Impressed, He Who Remains smiled and claimed that Loki was his favorite of the two Variants in front of him. As Loki took a seat, He Who Remains informed Loki that he was well aware of [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]]'s inability to fix the [[Temporal Loom]]. He Who Remains explained that the Temporal Loom was never intended to handle all the branched timelines but a failsafe that would delete all of the branches, the TVA included, in order to save the [[Sacred Timeline]]. He Who Remains then added that his Variants were already out there in the Multiverse.
[[File:HWR Leaning on Desk.png|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains gives [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] an ultimatum]]
Loki declared that he would destroy the Loom before it could delete the branches and destroy the TVA, although He Who Remains reminded him that the Loom prevented a [[Multiversal War|brutal war]] from breaking out, where all realities, including the Sacred Timeline, would be destroyed. He Who Remains implored Loki to see reason, claiming that Loki had known peace in his life because He Who Remains had presided at the [[Citadel at the End of Time]], and that he got to rule over the timeline because he was capable of making the tough choices.
[[File:Protect What We Can.png|{{AltFloat}}|He Who Remains tells [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] they have to protect what they can]]
When Loki once again declared that he would find another way, He Who Remains informed Loki that he would have to make one of two tough choices: allow Laufeydottir to kill him, thereby leading to the scenario where the Loom overloads and allows for a Multiversal War in which they would all die; or kill Laufeydottir so that he and Loki could work together to protect the Sacred Timeline. However, Loki chose to time slip away from the Citadel, eventually returning to the point in time before the Loom exploded. In doing so, Loki restored history to the version where Laufeydottir had killed He Who Remains, thereby undoing He Who Remains' resurrection.{{Ref|LK206}}

====Dethroned by Loki====
Having returned to the [[Time Variance Authority Office]] right before the [[Temporal Loom]] exploded, [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] decided to forge a third option for himself, where he would destroy the Loom itself, releasing the infinite branches of the [[Multiverse]] from its grip. As the branches began to die, Loki used his magic to revive them before transporting them, along with himself, to the [[Citadel at the End of Time]]. Loki then sat upon He Who Remains' throne and chose to hold the branches of the Multiverse himself for all time, allowing both the [[Sacred Timeline]] and the branched timelines to co-exist while giving the [[Time Variance Authority]] a chance to defend themselves against the Variants of He Who Remains who would one day arrive.{{Ref|LK206}}

==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
{{Quote|He's terrifying. He planned everything. He's seen everything. He knows everything.|[[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] to [[Mobius M. Mobius]] and [[Hunter B-15]]|For All Time. Always.}}
*'''Nigh-Omniscience''': Up until "the threshold," He Who Remains knew everything in the [[Sacred Timeline]]. In fact, He Who Remains planned everything that has ever happened in the [[Multiverse]] and was even aware of the actions of his Variants such as [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]]. Before [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] spoke, his words were already printed in He Who Remains' script, showing that everything they had done was designed and anticipated by He Who Remains before. As Loki soon learned, He Who Remains put in a failsafe after his death, knowing that his demise would lead to the [[Release of the Multiverse]] and thus create too many timelines for the [[Temporal Loom]], ensuring that his plans would still be active. He was also aware that Loki would start [[Time Slipping]], even making sure it happened in order to be resurrected later.

===Abilities===
{{Quote|And who do you think paved that road? Any guesses? Survey says..."<br>"He Who Remains."<br>"Bingo!|He Who Remains and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]|Glorious Purpose (Loki Season Two)}}
*'''Genius-Level Intellect''': He Who Remains had the intellect and foresight to create the [[Time Variance Authority]], a sprawling bureaucratic organization of enormous size and complexity. He also developed the protocols that the TVA used to pinpoint "Nexus Events" and prevent them from causing new timelines to branch off. He was successful at maintaining a single "[[Sacred Timeline]]" for millions of subjective years, and only failed in the end because he allowed himself to be found and defeated. He also had the intellect to tame and successfully weaponize [[Alioth]], a being made of all the tears in time, and make it the guardian of his castle. He also planned out a failsafe of the [[Temporal Loom]] to ensure that his efforts would not be in vain after his death. When [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] returned to fix the Temporal Loom, He Who Remains very easily deduced that Loki was from the future.
{{Quote|I understand your moral objections to what the [[TVA]] does. And my methods are deceptive. But the mission, it never was. Without the me, without the TVA... everything burns.|He Who Remains to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and [[Sylvie Laufeydottir]]|For All Time. Always.}}
*'''Master Tactician''': [[File:Sacred Timeline.jpg|thumb|250px|He Who Remains managing the [[Sacred Timeline]]]] He Who Remains was a mastermind capable of setting up incredibly complex and elaborate plans and carrying them out flawlessly. He established an entire false history of the [[Time Variance Authority]] for propaganda purposes, claiming that it was created by a trio of alien [[Time-Keepers]] and concealing the fact that its employees were Variants themselves. He also orchestrated an entire contingency plan to have himself resurrected should he be killed, involving guiding several individuals' actions posthumously to achieve this feat such as [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]'s [[Time Slipping]] and the [[Temporal Loom]].
{{Quote|Eons ago, before the [[TVA]], a Variant of myself lived on Earth in the 31st century. He was a scientist and he discovered that there were universes stacked on top of his own. At the same time, other versions of us were learning the same thing.|He Who Remains to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and [[Sylvie Laufeydottir]]|For All Time. Always.}}
*'''Master Scientist''': [[File:HWR Presentation.png|thumb|250px|He Who Remains successfully weaponizing [[Alioth]]]] He Who Remains was able to successfully configure both [[Alioth]] and [[Miss Minutes]] with his scientific ability.
*'''Master Engineer''': He Who Remains created the [[Temporal Loom]] to manage branched timelines as well as delete them when necessary as a means to preserve the [[Sacred Timeline]]. He also created lifelike androids dubbed the [[Time-Keepers]],  using them as proxies to control the TVA from the shadows. He was also one of very few people to successfully develop [[time travel]], and invented the highly advanced technology that the TVA uses to control the timestream.
*'''Master Combatant''': He Who Remains battled his other Variants and eventually succeeded, stopping the [[Multiversal War]].
*'''Staff Mastery''': During the [[Multiversal War]], He Who Remains used a [[Time Stick]] to fight his other Variants.

==Equipment==
*'''[[TemPad]]''': He Who Remains had an advanced TemPad that include many functions of the [[Time Variance Authority]] regular equipment. He used a function to produce a substance which could be morphed into various shapes such as figures of himself, his Variants, [[Alioth]], and the [[Multiverse]] when telling [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and [[Sylvie Laufeydottir]] about the [[Multiversal War]]. He Who Remains used the Time Twister function to evade Laufeydottir's attacks and to transport himself out of the elevator to his office.

===Former Equipment===
*'''[[Kang the Conqueror's Armor|Battle Armor]]''': During the [[Multiversal War]], He Who Remains wore a battle armor to fight his other Variants.

==Facilities==
{{Quote|Every step you took to get [[Citadel at the End of Time|here]], [[Escape from Lamentis-1|Lamentis]], The [[Void (End of Time)|Void]], I paved the road. You... You just walked down it.|He Who Remains to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and [[Sylvie Laufeydottir]]|For All Time. Always.}}
*'''[[Citadel at the End of Time]]''': After the [[Multiversal War]], He Who Remains settled in a castle, dubbed the Citadel at the End of Time, located on an asteroid. For eons, he took up residence at the castle and watched the sacred timeline.

