==Trivia==
*In the comics, He Who Remains is the last director of the [[Time Variance Authority]]. In the [[Citadel at the End of Time]], he created the [[w:c:marvel:Time-Twisters|Time-Twisters]] and [[Time-Keepers]].

==Behind the Scenes==
[[File:He Who Remains Concept Art 2.jpg|thumb|right|[[Immortus]]-inspired concept art]]
*The [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] version of the character was described by [[Kate Herron]] to be "closer to [[Immortus]]" than to He Who Remains from the comics, who is not an alternate version of [[Kang]]. She likened the situation to [[Sylvie Laufeydottir|Sylvie]]'s in which he is an original character that is inspired by different comic characters.<ref>''[https://gizmodo.com/loki-season-2-wont-feature-season-1-director-kate-herro-1847308990 Loki Season 2 Won't Feature Season 1 Director Kate Herron]''</ref> Immortus later debuted in the MCU with ''[[Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania]]''.
**According to [[Michael Waldron]], he pushed the idea to combine He Who Remains with "a little bit of [[Immortus]] mythology" very early on. He also confirmed that He Who Remains was always the endgame for [[Loki (TV series)/Season One|''Loki'' Season One]].<ref name="SacredTimeline"/>
**A piece of concept art drawn for He Who Remains has him in an outfit that resembles [[Immortus]].{{Ref|TAoLK}}
*[[David Charles Warren III]] was a stunt double for [[Jonathan Majors]] in the role of He Who Remains.
*[[Eric Martin]] revealed that in one version of the ''[[For All Time. Always.]]'' episode, there would be a vast display room where He Who Remains kept artifacts from the timeline, like a massive version of the one belonging to [[Ravonna Renslayer]].<ref>[https://twitter.com/MrEricMartin/status/1415525974146314249 Eric Martin on Twitter]</ref>
**Martin also described He Who Remains as "Almost like a young tech CEO. As much a genius as they are charlatan."
*According to [[Jonathan Majors]], He Who Remains' apparel came from different time periods. His cape came from the {{WPS|Victorian era}}, the shoes are from {{WPS|Genghis Khan}} himself and the pants are from [[Mongolia]].{{Ref|TMoLK}}
*In the original ending of ''[[Loki (TV series)|Loki]]'' [[Loki (TV series)/Season One|season one]], the statue towering over the [[TVA]] was actually another Kang rather than He Who Remains. This was retconned in [[Loki (TV series)/Season Two|season two]].<ref name="Herron">[https://www.btlnews.com/crafts/direction/loki-director-kate-herron/ Director Kate Herron Reveals Secrets of the Loki Universe (Spoilers Ahead!!)]</ref>

